sentences: Lois Kahn Wallace (May 25, 1940 - April 4, 2014) was a prominent American literary agent, known for her representation of numerous successful authors.
Born in Manhattan, she graduated from the Brearley School and Vassar College before taking a secretarial job for G.P. Putnam Sons in 1961.
She went to work for agent Harold Ober in 1963, then joined the William Morris Agency literary department in 1967, where she became co-director before establishing her own agency in 1974.
